    dc:title "Review of the genus Macropsis Lewis, 1836 (Homoptera: Auchenorrhyncha Cicadellidae: Eurymelinae: Macropsini) of Southeastern Kazakhstan with description of new species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457944>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404165>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457946>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404171> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948>
    dc:description "FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167>
    dc:description "FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457944>
    dc:description "FIGURES 48–81. Macropsis suspecta (48–54), M. vicina (55–61), M. tarbagataica (62–68), and M. iliensis (69–81). 48–49, 55–56, 62–63―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 50–51, 57–58, 64–65, 69, 71—the 2nd sternite; 52–53, 59–60, 66–67, 70, 72, 74, 77, 80―penis, lateral view; 54, 61, 68, 75, 78, 81―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor; 73, 76, 79―male 2nd abdominal apodemes. 69–70―paratype of M. iliensis; 71–72―paratype of M. tuvensis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4457944/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404165>
    dc:description "FIGURES 5–28. Macropsis spp., lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4404165/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457946>
    dc:description "FIGURES 126–150. Macropsis milkoi (126–138), M. cerea (139–144), and M. viridobrunnea (145–150). 126, 130, 134, 139, 145―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 127–128, 131–132, 135–136, 140–141, 146–147—the 2nd sternite; 129, 133, 137, 142–143, 148–149―penis, lateral view; 138, 144, 150―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4457946/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404171>
    dc:description "FIGURES 92–111. Macropsis notata (92–96), M. ocellata (97–101), M. gravesteini (102–106), and M. prasina (107–111) from European Russia (92–93, 97–98, 102–103, 107–109) and Southeastern Kazakhstan (94–96, 99–101, 104–106, 110–111). 92, 94, 97, 99, 102, 104, 107, 110―male 2nd abdominal apodemes; 93, 95, 98, 100, 103, 105, 108, 111―penis, lateral view; 96, 101, 106, 109―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4404171/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

